content: The USS Arizona model caught my attention because of the level of detail and realism achieved by the builder. It reminded me of how much I enjoyed building models as a kid and made me want to try it again. As for getting back into it, the most challenging part has been getting my painting skills back up to par. It's funny, I used to think I was pretty good at it, but after a 2-year break, I realized how rusty I was!
